# API Contract

- Design or update OpenAPI before implementing an externally visible endpoint.
- Version public routes under `/api/v1`; make operations resource-oriented and idempotent.
- Use explicit request and response schemas with stable operation IDs.
- Represent errors with one documented envelope and machine-readable error codes.
- Use RFC 3339 UTC timestamps and opaque string identifiers.
- Define pagination, filtering, ordering, and concurrency tokens in the contract.
- Do not expose Kubernetes API objects as the product API.
- Generate client artifacts from the contract; never edit generated files manually.
- Treat incompatible schema changes as migrations requiring an ADR.
